The diary contains the personal entries of the high priestess. She apparently
only chose to record events of great personal significance. The first entry is:

Marpenoth 10: A travelling evangelist named Elgar visited our cathedral today.
	He is a follower of Mitra who hails from the city of Darkwind far to
	the south. Apparently the practices of this church failed to impress
	the righteous Elgar, for he delivered a scathing sermon on the evils
	of falling from Mitra's grace, and the perils of having an imperfect
	leader. I think this Elgar needs to look to his own arrogance before
	looking for sins in others. It seems he is at least right about one
	thing. I am hardly a perfect leader for this church. A true holy
	priestess would not have been moved by his harsh words, but, alas,
	I feel my anger rise at the mere memory of him. No further visitors
	from Darkwind will be welcome at this church.

	

